  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00012_197412_1517807319698&sectionId=33191&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00012_197412_1517807319698
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Economic Offences`
  line `(Inapplicability of Limitation) Act, 1974.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the territories to which the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) applies.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on the 1st day of April, 1974.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (33192)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Chapter XXXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 not to apply to certain offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 65 of 1984, s. 10 (w.e.f. 8-10-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00012_197412_1517807319698&sectionId=33192&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00012_197412_1517807319698
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in Chapter XXXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) shall apply to--`
  line
  line `(i) any offence punishable under any of the enactments ^1`
  line `[or provisions, if any, thereof] specified`
  line `in the Schedule; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any other offence, which under the provisions of that Code, may be tried along with such`
  line offence,
  line
  line `and every offence referred to in clause (i) or clause (ii) may be taken cognizance of by the Court having`
  line `jurisdiction as if the provisions of that Chapter were not enacted.`
